<subSubSection id="FECD93DF26A475203F98F0A0DC08F05D" pageId="7" pageNumber="128" type="pollen">
<paragraph id="0B78946253D53D7D408A75EE9FFAD8A8" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Pollen.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C8179804B59FB9C5C5766EA08CE31835" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">
trizonocolpate to pantocolpate, radially symmetrical, isopolar with circular or convex-quadrangular contour in polar view. 
<emphasis id="155FA58BF2196AC35F602903F42B81F7" bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Shape</emphasis>
: prolate-spheroidal (P/E=1.04-1.12). 
<emphasis id="57DE6DDAD2F9E870D5D837199A775581" bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Apertures</emphasis>
: 3 or 12, brevicolpate to colpate; polar area medium-sized to large (PAI=0.41-0.60). 
<emphasis id="BE3F73AF66BB44EA03F6836AC9B4E888" bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Measurements</emphasis>
: pollen grains large to very large, (50.9)77.50(100.2) 
<normalizedToken id="C411F004505BB9B8EB0E1EF481782E1A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(66.79)82.21(100.86) 
<normalizedToken id="F6E702DF09E428D78C5974E4C1385EBC" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in equatorial view; exine thickness (2.29)2.96(3.77) 
<normalizedToken id="7213BF10F48CF5E9F532D7831D137048" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. 
<emphasis id="B101FFF44FE6017E082C90737DA47AF7" bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Ornamentation</emphasis>
: smooth surface with tectum perforate, ornated with spinules of (1.12)1.48(1.82) 
<normalizedToken id="5D382D468ADD7FC08819D791EC092710" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
length 
<normalizedToken id="8608D31743DB12F5FE71B99D7C7E84F9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(1.13)1.44(1.91) 
<normalizedToken id="9C771EC6156CEECEDF69D5D24E8CD087" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
diameter in base; perforations (0.17)0.29(0.50) 
<normalizedToken id="AB96B7B4904B07936758B2DB22E05E2D" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diameter (
<figureCitation id="D175B3D9497C8DDD01CEC2736A8D2369" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Pollen grains of tribe Hylocereeae (Scanning Electron Microscope photographs). A-D: Left polar view, right equatorial view A S. undatus (C. Ruiz et al. 560) B Weberocereus tunilla (C. K. Horich BGA 58344) C S. setaceus (H. Bravo et al. 2755). D-J: left polar view, left details of spinules and perforations D S. megalanthus (C. Ruiz et al. 563) E S. stenopterus (C. K. Horich s. n.) F S. triangularis (C. Gomez-Hinostrosa 2110) G Kimnachia ramulosa (L. Velasquez et al. 4884) H Pseudorhipsalis amazonica (E. Gudino 145) I S. alliodorus (A. Ruiz Velazco et al. 86) J S. glaber (C. K. Horich BGA 57239)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.128.35842.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/326049" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Figure 4I</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="890468E42FEFA69D1B14BAA59AD6F514" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Pollen grains of tribe Hylocereeae (Scanning Electron Microscope photographs). A-D: Left polar view, right equatorial view A S. undatus (C. Ruiz et al. 560) B Weberocereus tunilla (C. K. Horich BGA 58344) C S. setaceus (H. Bravo et al. 2755). D-J: left polar view, left details of spinules and perforations D S. megalanthus (C. Ruiz et al. 563) E S. stenopterus (C. K. Horich s. n.) F S. triangularis (C. Gomez-Hinostrosa 2110) G Kimnachia ramulosa (L. Velasquez et al. 4884) H Pseudorhipsalis amazonica (E. Gudino 145) I S. alliodorus (A. Ruiz Velazco et al. 86) J S. glaber (C. K. Horich BGA 57239)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.128.35842.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/326049" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">4J</figureCitation>
